  "detailedRequirements": "<h2>1.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; System Description</h2>\n\n<p>The client for this project built a platform that supports the sale, exchange, and redemption of gift cards between businesses and individuals.&nbsp; The goal of this platform is to help small businesses expand, using both web and mobile layouts, by giving them a simple way to raise capital and acquire new&nbsp;customers using gift cards. &nbsp;The main function of the platform will be to allow business to post virtual gift cards for sale on the platform.&nbsp; Individual users will be able to browse and buy these gift cards, as well as resell or trade gift cards they own.&nbsp; Using the mobile layout, users will be able to redeem their gift cards at the business, and the business will be able to process gift card redemption at their point of sale.</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">A brief description of the workflow is attached. The platform is already live&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://foundershare.com/#/\" style=\"line-height: 18.9091px;\">https://foundershare.com</a><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">but requires various enhancements to satisfy all user needs.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">You can also check out the Sandbox at&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://qa.foundershare.com/#/\" style=\"line-height: 1.6;\">https://qa.foundershare.com/#/</a><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">&nbsp;to pass the end-to-end flow without paying with a real credit card (just a fake one number 4111 1111 1111 1111 is enough).</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">This challenge is responsible for implementing Saving user&#39;s payment method to Braintree vault.</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div style=\"font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; padding: 5px 10px; margin: 0px; line-height: 18.9091px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\"><span style=\"font-size:15.2728px\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255, 255, 0)\">The assembly is a part of Founder$hare Code Blitz. See&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codeblitz.wpengine.com\">details</a>.</span></strong></span></span></div>\n\n<div class=\"previewMask\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\">\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\">1.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Competition Task Overview</span></h2>\n\n<div style=\"padding: 5px 10px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18.9091px; font-size: 12.7273px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 0, 0)\"><span class=\"marker\"><strong>Time constraint</strong></span></span></div>\n\n<div style=\"padding: 5px 10px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18.9091px; font-size: 12.7273px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 0, 0)\"><span class=\"marker\">This project has tight timeline so</span></span></div>\n\n<div style=\"padding: 5px 10px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18.9091px; font-size: 12.7273px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 0, 0)\"><span class=\"marker\">1) the review phase is only 24 hours</span></span></div>\n\n<div style=\"padding: 5px 10px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18.9091px; font-size: 12.7273px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background: rgb(238, 238, 238);\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 0, 0)\"><span class=\"marker\">2) we would like to avoid any timeline extension, please ask questions early</span></span></div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\"><strong>1.2.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scope.&nbsp;</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p><u><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\"><strong>PMP-231.&nbsp;</strong></span><strong><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size:14px\">Both desktop and mobile.</span></strong></u></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Use case 1.<br />\n1. When signed-in Champion is on the Payment page entering their credit card details, there must be a checkbox &quot;Save your credit card details&quot; the braintree widget (or as a part of Braintree widget).<br />\n2. When Champions clicks &quot;Pay&quot; and the credit card is valid</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Then&nbsp;{<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">If &quot;Save your credit card details&quot; box is TRUE Then save the credit card details}</span></span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">3. Multiple (up to 10) credit cards can be saved. The one saved for the last time is marked as default.<br />\n4. If the credit card is already saved for this account it shall NOT be saved twice, and user must be notified he already saved this card.</span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Use case 2.<br />\n1. When a signed-in Champion is on the Payment page</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Then</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">If there is 1 credit card saved for this account Then it must be pre-populated in the Braintree payment widget;</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">If there is multiple credit cards saved for this account Then it Champion must be provided with the list of credit cards to choose from; the chosen one is pre-populated the Braintree payment widget.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size:14px\">When viewing the list of credit card to choose user must be able to remove the payment method from the saved ones. That means the method will be removed at the Braintree side and the token removed at the F$ back-end side.</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Impl notes:</strong><br />\na) credit card details must NOT be stored in cookies or browser session;<br />\nb) Use the vault via Braintree, and its node.js SDK&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developers.braintreepayments.com/guides/customers/node\">https://developers.braintreepayments.com/guides/customers/node</a></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">c) the technical flow is the following:</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;- when saving credit card details, save customer into braintree first and save generated customer id into database.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;- save payment method(like credit card, Paypal) into braintree and save the generated paymentMethodToken into database.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;- &nbsp;when champion lands the payment page, retrieve info of payment method from braintree and show them on frontend page.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;- &nbsp;pre-populate selected credit cards on the payment page.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0)\"><strong>PMP-232.&nbsp;</strong></span><strong><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size:14px\">Mobile.</span></strong></u></p>\n\n<div>\n<p>If user doesn&#39;t have any more gift cards for a buiness but there is a few $ gap in redemption, suggest buying another gift card immediately.</p>\nIF her credit card details are stored THEN do it automatically after she agrees: ask a question and user will tap YES button to confirm or NO button to reject;<br />\nELSE ask to enter card details manually (redirecting to the payment page).</div>\n</div>\n",
